MEDIA HANDLINGPIC: Director, HRAlternate: Communications Executive1) Prepare Statements, arrange for press briefings / press conference: if and as needed.2) Handle media communication in consultation with the Managing Director.3) Maintain a record of incoming media queries and outgoing media statements.4) Monitor media coverage and update the MD and ERT.5) Prepare fact sheet for the MD & ERT.6) Arranges press conferences, interviews and site tours. Ensures company employees are kept informed.7) A Communication Team shall be mobilized if necessary and assigned a dedicated extension number, which shall be notified to thereception.5. BUSINESS CONTINUITYPIC: Managing DirectorAlternate: Director HR1) Advise Incident Commander on public affairs implications of incident features, management decisions and response measures.2) Liaises with government authorities and other stakeholders, including NGOs.6. TECHNICAL SUPPORTPIC: Technical SuperintendentAlternate: Back-up Technical Superintendent 1) Main Contact with the vessel.2) Develops tactical plans to implement incident objectives.3) Manages operations directly or ensures their implementation in-field by appropriate local direction.4) Liaises with Logistics to ensure resources are available to carry out response measures.5) Reports on operations in progress and any adjustment necessary.6) Advises on ‘Health and Safety’ issues at the outset, to ensure conditions are safe at the incident site.7) Ensures risk assessments, site safety plans and safety precautions/ procedures are implemented at all appropriate responselocations.8) Prepare/ Update ‘Situation Report’ (SitRep) for Incident Commander.9) Supervises ‘Field Command Post’, Logistic Chief and Navigational Support team.7. TECHNICAL ADVICEPIC: General Manager Tech & OperationsAlternate: Sr Technical Superintendent1) Identifies short/ medium/ long term planning2) Information gathering, evaluation and dissemination3) Monitors incident potential and worst case scenarios4) Assists Operations Chief, Incident Commander.8. LOGISTICSPIC: Vessel’s Technical SuperintendentAlternate: Back-up Technical Superintendent1) Provision of facilities, services and material including clean up contractor, Emergency Towing, Salvage, Helicopter , Shipyard, repairyards etc.2) Coordinates and processes requests for additional resources3) Advises on future support resource needs4) Handles security, medical, food, field communication, equipment and material supplies/ facilities on site.5) Liase with other Contractors. 9. NAVIGATION & OperationsPIC: Operations ManagerAlternate: Sr Marine Superintendent1) Obtains relevant information for Charts/ port data, Tides/ Currents and weather forecasts and updates ‘Incident Commander’accordingly.2) Consults ‘Class - Emergency Technical Assistance’ on matters concerning vessel stability and integrity, cargo, water influx, damagestability calculations etc and updates ‘Incident Commander’ accordingly.
